definition: dammed lake/lake formed by landslip or lava flow
Serbia/Serbian/abbr. for 塞爾維亞|塞尔维亚[Sai1 er3 wei2 ya4]
to stop up/to squeeze in/to stuff/cork/stopper
to stop up/to stuff/to cope with

sentences.english: In early July 2010, the lake finally began flowing over the spillway.
sentences.chinese: 2010年7月初，堰塞湖终于通过泄洪渠开始放水。

sentences.english: The river was jammed up by a landslide, now that may burst.
sentences.chinese: 河流现在由于泥石流挤成了堰塞湖，现在可能溃堤。

sentences.english: The quake lake is naturally formed by complete damming of a river.
sentences.chinese: 堰塞湖是由于天然坝的完全堵江蓄水而形成。

sentences.english: The aim of the army is the Tangjiashan quake lake located at the upper reaches of the Beichuan County.
sentences.chinese: 部队的目标，是位于北川县城上游的唐家山堰塞湖。

sentences.english: Xinhua says the water level in Tangjiashan lake is half drained.
sentences.chinese: 新华社还说，唐家山堰塞湖的水位降低了一半。

sentences.english: Water from the lake on Jianjiang River flowed into the Fujiang River that runs through Mianyang city.
sentences.chinese: 导出的涧江上堰塞湖的水注入到了流经绵阳的涪江。

sentences.english: Rescue teams on top of the Tangjiashan quake lake dam are using solar power to illuminate the site.
sentences.chinese: 唐家山堰塞湖坝顶抢险部队用太阳能照明。

sentences.english: Rescuers are ready to dynamite Tangjiashan barrier lake.
sentences.chinese: 救援者已准备好炸破唐家山堰塞湖。
